# --- Microsoft Clarity (optional UX analytics) ---
# Project ID from https://clarity.microsoft.com/ → Project → Settings. Omit locally to disable.
# Production: set this in your host (e.g. Vercel) as a build env so Vite embeds it at build time.
# VITE_CLARITY_PROJECT_ID=

# --- Vercel APIs: scene board + mailing list ---
# Point this at your deployed app origin (no trailing slash) when `npm run dev` should call
# production `/api/scene-board` and `/api/mailing-list` (local Vite has no API routes).
# VITE_SCENE_BOARD_API_URL=https://your-app.vercel.app
#
# Vercel + Supabase integration (or manual): client `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` + anon/publishable
# key, or the same as `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` + `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`. Server functions accept
# `SUPABASE_URL` (or the same URL on `NEXT_PUBLIC_`), and `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` or
# `SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY` plus `SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET` (or optional `SCENE_BOARD_JWT_SECRET` for
# scene board HMAC; see `app/api/lib/supabaseServerEnv.ts`).
# Optional: PLATFORM_OWNER_PUBKEY for /api/mailing-list admin — defaults to the same built-in
# owner as VITE_PLATFORM_OWNER_PUBKEY / app/src/config/platformOwner.ts.

# After deploy, set if your program id differs from the scaffold keypair.
VITE_STAKE_TO_CURATE_PROGRAM_ID=UfaPFjHzepp91cEzmfoAd2b7bMVWoB37wuPRa8vy9Su

# Optional: base58 pubkey allowed to open **Dashboard** in the wallet menu (defaults to the
# SnapCinema platform owner). Forks can set their own admin wallet.
# VITE_PLATFORM_OWNER_PUBKEY=YourAdminWalletPubkeyHere

# Shared demo slot (recommended for Watch): base58 pubkey of the wallet that
# runs Dashboard → "Setup demo (init slot only)" once. All viewers use this slot without
# initializing. Omit for local solo dev (connected wallet = slot authority).
# VITE_STAKE_SLOT_AUTHORITY=YourAdminWalletPubkeyHere

# On-chain slot index 0–255 (default 0). Bump to 1, 2, … then restart Vite and
# run "Setup demo" again for a clean slate (new vault + scenes); old slot data
# stays on devnet but the app no longer points at it.
# VITE_DEMO_SLOT_ID=0

# Optional: Account page — show illustrative "Yield preview" card (not on-chain; hackathon demo).
# VITE_ACCOUNT_YIELD_PREVIEW=true

# Optional: Fan tab video URLs (defaults to /demo-v0.mp4 and /demo-v1.mp4 in public/).
# VITE_DEMO_VIDEO_V0=https://example.com/cut-a.mp4
# VITE_DEMO_VIDEO_V1=https://example.com/cut-b.mp4

# Watch page: YouTube Short or any embeddable YouTube video id, or full embed URL.
# VITE_YOUTUBE_SHORT_ID=dQw4w9WgXcQ
# VITE_YOUTUBE_EMBED_URL=https://www.youtube.com/embed/VIDEO_ID?rel=0

# Optional: Helius / Triton / local node (defaults to public devnet RPC).
# Must match the cluster selected in the wallet (e.g. Phantom → Devnet, not Testnet).
# VITE_SOLANA_RPC=https://api.devnet.solana.com

# --- JitoSOL / Kamino (Dashboard, mainnet only) ---
# Enables Kamino dashboard + withdraw in the app when the wallet uses **mainnet** RPC.
# Reaction stakes still use StakeToCurate’s vault on your configured cluster; this flag does
# not move vault SOL — see programs/stake_to_curate/README.md (“Vault vs external DeFi”).
# VITE_ENABLE_YIELD_BOOST=true
# Optional: override the default JitoSOL/SOL Kamino strategy pubkey (multipool).
# VITE_KAMINO_JITOSOL_SOL_STRATEGY=4Zuhh9SD6iQyaPx9vTt2cqHpAcwM7JDvUMkqNmyv6oSD
# Optional: UI APY midpoint for admin reference copy (default 8).
# VITE_YIELD_BOOST_APY_PERCENT=8

# --- Immediate yield worker (Node, mainnet; no Vite) ---
# After `configure_yield_treasury` (Dashboard), run from `app/`:
#   TREASURY_KEYPAIR=~/.config/solana/id.json STAKE_SLOT_AUTHORITY=<base58> SOLANA_RPC=https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com npm run immediate-yield-worker
# Optional: STAKE_TO_CURATE_PROGRAM_ID, STAKE_DEMO_SLOT_ID, KAMINO_JITOSOL_SOL_STRATEGY, YIELD_WORKER_POLL_MS

# Verbose Watch playlist weight / RNG logs in the browser console (default on in dev).
# VITE_DEBUG_PLAYLIST=false
# Or: localStorage.snapcinema_debug_playlist = '1' to force on, '0' to force off.
